# Changelog

### v2.2.3
- New: XML module now supports CDATA sections (`<![CDATA[...]]>`) â€” parse and serialize as text nodes.
- New: XML module now supports Processing Instructions (`<?target data?>`) â€” new `Type::ProcessingInstruction` node type with `create_processing_instruction()`, `pi_target()`, `pi_data()` accessors, and `processing_instructions()` generator.
- New: XML module now supports `xml:space="preserve"` attribute with inheritance â€” controls whitespace trimming on text content; `xml:space="default"` overrides back to trimming.
- New: XML module is now standalone (`[SCL_STANDALONE_MODULE]`) â€” expanded `enable_copy_move` and `scl2_enum_bitop` macros to remove `basics.hpp` and `enum.hpp` dependencies; removed `bytearray`/`stringlist` forward declarations and `payload()` method. Only depends on standard library.
- New: Added `doc/xml.md` â€” dedicated documentation file replacing the inline theory block in the header.
- New: Added `Type` enum (`Element`, `Text`, `Comment`, `ProcessingInstruction`) with `is_element()`, `is_text()`, `is_comment()`, `is_processing_instruction()` helpers.
- New: Added `elements()`, `comments()`, `processing_instructions()` generator functions for filtered child iteration.
- New: Added `create_comment()`, `create_text()`, `create_processing_instruction()` static factory methods.
- Changed: `deserialize()` now accepts `preserve_whitespace` parameter.
- Changed: Header comment now references W3C XML 1.0 (Fifth Edition) specification.
- Fix: XML self-closing tag serialization used `&&` instead of `||` â€” nodes with children but no attributes/text were incorrectly serialized as self-closing.
- Fix: XML attribute parsing didn't handle `/` in self-closing tags â€” `/` was treated as an attribute name.
- Fix: XML name extraction included `<` character due to using `tag_start` instead of `tag_start + 1`.
- Build: `cpp_generation` set to `cxx23` (requires `<generator>`).

### v2.2.2
- New: `condition_parser` module extracted from `condition.cpp` into separate `condition_parser.hpp`/`.cpp` with template-based `ConditionParser<Tokenizer_Type>` supporting `DefaultTokenizer` (prefix `!` NOT, `&|^` operators, `->`/`<-` implication) and `NormalTokenizer` (postfix `'` NOT, word-style bool literals).
- New: `condition_node::parseNormal()` for parsing expressions in "normal" format.
- New: Added `condition_parser_inst.cpp` with explicit template instantiations.
- Fix: `bytearray_view::read<T>()` for trivially copyable types was missing `cursor += sizeof(_T)` â€” acted as `peek()` instead of `read()`.
- Fix: Implication evaluation in `logical.hpp` â€” corrected `Imply_Left`/`Imply_Right` return values; fixed operator mapping (`->` now maps to `Imply_Left` as expected).
- Fix: Postfix NOT (`A'`) support added in `NormalTokenizer` parse logic.
- Fix: `condition_parser` postfix NOT handling â€” moved from `parsePrimary()` to proper tokenizer-level support.
- Build: `condition_parser.cpp` explicit instantiations moved from `.cpp` to `condition_parser_inst.cpp`.

