### v1.22.6
- **IMPORTANT** Bug fix: bytearray constructor for trivially copyable types now correctly assigns data instead of inserting, preventing unintended resizing and data corruption. Also, size based constructor added.
- Note: If you need to store a size_t into bytearray, use the std::bytearray<size_t>( mysize ) or it will just create a bytearray with sizeof(size_t) bytes, which is not what you want. Or, create an empty one and use append(), which is guaranteed to work correctly.

